(In reply to comment #3)
> This might be a good chance to remove the widget in general. I'm not sure if
> thats a good idea and the community needs the flash widget so we should check
> that before thinking about a removal.

IMHO, abandoning the widget might not be the best solution:
1. Flash is almost dead in the mobile platforms but is still well alive in desktop platforms, for which qooxdoo support has been great;
2. Personally, I don't use that widget (as we use SVG instead) but I believe many will still find it useful;
3. We've developed a similar widget for embedding SVG (not in the same scope of the contrib, which is to provide a canvas-like) and, although in production, it was never contributed as it needs further polishing to match qooxdoo standards;
4. I've already hinted in the past towards providing even further media embedding support (such as audio), although there wasn't much reception.

Disclaimer: I haven't been following other interaction channels, such as the mailing list.
